{
  "texts": [
    "Making algorithmic alterations appears to have been most effective at mitigating measurement bias, but this is an extremely small sample (n=2) [33,36].",
    "Overall, these findings highlight the complexity and context-dependence of mitigating age-related bias in ML models.",
    "While some strategies showed promising results, achieving complete elimination of bias remains challenging, and alternative approaches may need to be explored.",
    "Researchers must consider how both the data and the models they are using may affect outcomes.Our second research question explored the types of bias being mitigated.",
    "Our previous work has demonstrated that age-related bias is present across the ML life cycle [9]."
  ]
}